{"title": "Evelyn; or A Heart Unmasked", "description": "Evelyn is a two-volume novel told in an epistolary style \u2013 alternating between letters from the point of view of a trusted, unmarried female friend of the young, na\u00efve heroine of the novel and those of the feckless adventurer who decides that he must seduce the beautiful Evelyn.  \nThe author, actress/novelist/playwright Anna Cora Mowatt, was a fan of the works of Fredericka Bremer (early feminist author, sometimes called the \u201cSwedish Jane Austen\u201d).  This narrative is heavily influenced by that writer\u2019s style. Like Mowatt\u2019s hit comedy, \u201cFashion,\u201d the plot centers on the misadventures of nouveau riche family social climbing in New York society of the late 1830\u2019s.  Whereas the play was comedy, the novel turns towards tragedy.  The author still spices her narrative with strong doses of social satire, however, and gives us many revealing glimpses of everyday life of New Yorkers of the early 19th century.\n - Summary by Kelly S. Taylor", "duration": 57451, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "14763", "name": "Anna Cora Mowatt Ritchie"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/evelyn_or_a_heart_unmasked_2011_librivox/evelyn_2011.jpg", "copyright_year": "1845", "genres": ["Romance"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Kelly S. Taylor"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Kelly S. Taylor"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "DaveC"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Rapunzelina"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Vol I Chapter 1", "readers": [13852], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/evelyn_or_a_heart_unmasked_2011_librivox/evelyn_01_mowatt_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1892}, {"section": 2, "title": "Vol I Chapter 2", "readers": [13852], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/evelyn_or_a_heart_unmasked_2011_librivox/evelyn_02_mowatt_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1300}, {"section": 3, "title": "Vol I Chapter 3", "readers": [13852], "path": "htt